rporate org chart abstract ai\\\" style=\\\"width: 900px; height: 550px; background-color: #e2e8f0; border-radius: 4px; overflow: hidden; box-shadow: 0 10px 30px rgba(0,0,0,0.1); margin-bottom: 60px; position: relative; background-image: url('https://storage.mirra.my/media/carousel-images/3a1cd97d-f219-44f3-9bb8-c13f63b22349.jpg');  background-size: cover; background-position: center;\\\">\\n    </div>\\n\\n    <!-- Text Description -->\\n    <div style=\\\"width: 900px; text-align: center;\\\">\\n      <p style=\\\"font-size: 36px; line-height: 1.6; color: #4A4A4A; font-weight: 400; font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;\\\">\\n        Human companies look the way they do because of human limitations. Dunbar numbers. Management capacity.<br><br>\\n        AI has none of these constraints. So why copy paste the org chart?\\n      </p>\\n    </div>\\n\\n    <!-- Bottom Accent Bar -->\\n    <div style=\\\"position: absolute; bottom: 0; left: 0; width: 100%; height: 20px; background-color: #FFCE1F;\\\"></div>\\n  </div>\",\"pageNumber\":5},{\"html\":\"\\n    <link rel=\\\"preconnect\\\" href=\\\"https://fonts.googleapis.com\\\">\\n    <link rel=\\\"preconnect\\\" href=\\\"https://fonts.gstatic.com\\\" crossorigin=\\\"\\\">\\n    <link rel=\\\"preconnect\\\" href=\\\"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net\\\">\\n  \\n<link rel=\\\"stylesheet\\\" href=\\\"https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Inter:wght@400;500;600;700;800;900&amp;display=swap\\\">\\n<div style=\\\"width: 1080px; height: 1350px; overflow: hidden; position: relative; background-color: #333;\\\">\\n    \\n    <!-- Background Image -->\\n    <div data-slot-id=\\\"auto-slot-1\\\" class=\\\"image-slot\\\" data-slot-type=\\\"background\\\" data-slot-label=\\\"Wake Up Background\\\" data-search-query=\\\"sunrise clear path forward success\\\" style=\\\"position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; width: 100%; height: 100%; z-index: 1; background-image: url('https://storage.mirra.my/media/carousel-images/db7209a2-5b5b-4e51-bb06-fc84384